Politics

As of March 2011, Princeton had a total of 18,049 registered voters (combining the former borough and township). Among these, 9,184 (50.9%) were registered as [Democrats](/Democratic_Party_(United_States)), 2,140 (11.9%) as [Republicans](/Republican_Party_(United_States)), and 6,703 (37.1%) as [unaffiliated](/Unaffiliated_(New_Jersey)). An additional 22 voters were registered with the [Libertarian Party (United States)](/Libertarian_Party_(United_States)) or the [Green Party (United States)](/Green_Party_(United_States)). [87]

